French Builders Bid for London Project on Barratt Exit, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-06-08T00:19:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-08/french-builders-bid-for-london-project-on-barratt-exit-ft-says.html
French construction companies
 Bouygues SA (BOUY) , in partnership with private-equity firm The Carlyle
Group, and  Vinci SA (DG) , together with U.K. regeneration specialist
 St Modwen Properties Plc (SMP) , are competing for a 1 billion-pound
residential project at the 57-acre New Covent Garden Market in
south  London , after U.K. builder  Barratt Developments Plc (BDEV) 
withdrew from the bidding, the Financial Times reported, without
attribution.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 